records.addlTxt:
Count 1 - OWI (6th) - No contest plea.   
Count 3 - OAR - No contest plea.  Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, operate with PAC over .02%.  Motion granted.  Count 3 - OAR - Defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for one (1) year, under the Huber Law, to commence immediately.  Court costs are waived.  
Count 1 - OWI (6th) - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of five (5) years, two (2) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision imposed and stayed.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend one (1) year in jail, under the Huber Law, consecutive to the sentence imposed on Count 3;
2) Pay $2,400.00 fine, plus costs, total of $4,051.00;
3) Defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle unless agent approves it;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
7) Pay costs of action;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Three (3) year revocation of operating privileges.
Three (3) year ignition interlock.
Defendant is given credit for 2 days served.  
$500.00 cash bail to be applied to fine and costs.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. 
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment. 
Court Order for Intoxicated Driver Assessment and Driver Safety Plan.
Minutes.
